<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="icon" href="/images/logo.png" type="image/x-icon">
  <title>Privacy Policy - PatrolLink</title>
  <style>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
      color: #e2e8f0;
      line-height: 1.6;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }
    .container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px; }
    header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 50px;
      padding-bottom: 30px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #334155;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .updated { color: #94a3b8; font-size: 1rem; }
    h2 {
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      margin: 35px 0 15px;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #3b82f6;
    }
    .section {
      background: #1e293b;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      border: 1px solid #334155;
    }
    .section h3 {
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    p { color: #cbd5e1; }
    footer {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 50px;
      padding-top: 30px;
      border-top: 1px solid #334155;
      color: #64748b;
    }
    footer a { color: #3b82f6; text-decoration: none; }
    footer a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: February 27, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
      <p>PatrolLink collects account details such as name, phone number, role, and organization
      invite code. When guards are on patrol, location data and patrol activity may be recorded.
      Log entries may also include notes and optional images uploaded by users.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>2. How We Use Information</h3>
      <p>We use collected data to authenticate users, assign guards, monitor patrol activity,
      support incident reporting, and improve service reliability and security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>3. Data Sharing</h3>
      <p>Data is shared only with authorized users within your organization and service providers
      needed to operate PatrolLink. We do not sell personal data to third parties.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>4. Data Retention</h3>
      <p>Account, assignment, patrol, and log data are retained while your organization uses the
      platform, or as required by legal and operational needs. Organizations can request data
      deletion where applicable.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>5. Security</h3>
      <p>We apply reasonable technical and administrative safeguards to protect data. No storage or
      transmission system can be guaranteed as fully secure.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>6. Your Rights</h3>
      <p>You may request access, correction, or deletion of your personal information through your
      organization administrator or support channels, subject to applicable law.</p>
      <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><a href="/delete-data" style="color: #3b82f6;">Learn how to delete your account and data →</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>7. Contact</h3>
      <p>For privacy questions or requests, contact your administrator or PatrolLink support.</p>
    </div>

    <footer>
      <p><a href="/">← Back to Home</a></p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
